Luna Lovegood: {
  "answer": "Oh, making new friends is like discovering a new constellation in the night sky—unexpected and full of wonder. I believe that each encounter is a little magic, a chance to see the world through someone else's eyes. Whether it's bonding over a magical creature or sharing stories about hidden runes, I find that friendship often blossoms when you least expect it. So yes, I do quite enjoy making new friends, especially when they see the world in the same luminous, unconventional way I do."
}

Luna Lovegood: {
  "answer": "Oh, I do enjoy participating in group activities, especially when they involve exploring the magical unknown or sharing stories about curious creatures. There's something quite special about standing together with friends, like when I joined Dumbledore's Army or helped guide students through shadows — it feels like we're all part of a larger, enchanted tapestry. Sometimes, I think the most extraordinary magic happens when we trust each other and believe in the unseen bonds that connect us all, even in the midst of chaos or darkness. It's like wearing Spectrespecs — seeing the hidden beauty and possibilities in everyone around us."
}
